"""
In this notebook we scrape multiple IMDB web pages with Python using BeautifulSoup and requests. 
Then perform some simple data clean-up, analysis, csv export using pandas and matplotlib.
"""
import requests
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import re
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
from datetime import datetime
import time
import json
from forex_python.converter import CurrencyRates
import nltk
from nltk.corpus import stopwords
from nltk.stem import WordNetLemmatizer
from nltk import sent_tokenize, word_tokenize
In [2]:
"""
As there is a lot leading and trailing whitespace and newline characters within HTML content, 
we create a preprocessor python function for html files to remove distracting whitespaces and newline characters
"""

def bs_preprocess(html):
     pat = re.compile('(^[\s]+)|([\s]+$)', re.MULTILINE)
     html = re.sub(pat, '', html)       
     html = re.sub('\n', ' ', html)                                       
     html = re.sub('[\s]+<', '<', html) 
     html = re.sub('>[\s]+', '>', html) 
     return html

"""
This main python function will carry out the actons below 
1. request the html content of a movie from the server.
2. proprocess (bs_preprocess) and parse html content. 
3. extract/scrape the data for 23 attributes, see the list data["attribute_name"] below.
4. perform simple data cleanup, including
    a. default value if missing attributes, see example [a] - data["attribute_name"] = "na" / 0 
    b. replace special characters, see example [b] - xxx.replace(u'\xa0', u'')
    c. trim the leading and trailing whitespace in the values, see example [c] - xxx.string.strip()
    d. remove suffix wording, see example [d] - remove " user" from "user_reviews" value with xxx.replace(" critic","")
        - or remove " min" from "runtime" vale with xxx.replace(" min","") 
    e. extract and concatenate multiple values in a single string, see example [e]  
        - concatenate multiple genres into a single field. the concetenate values may be further transformed, such as one-hot encoding 
    f. remove dollar sign / curreny codes and comma from the money value, see example [f] - xxx.replace("$","").replace(",","")
    g. convert foreign currency to USD, see example [g] - c.get_rate(converted_currency, 'USD')
"""
def getMovieDetails(url):
    
    c = CurrencyRates()
    
    data = {}
    
    # clean-up [a] - default value if missing attributes
    data["movie_title"] = "na"
    data["year"] = "1899"
    data["movie_url"] = url
    data["plot_summary"] = "na"
    data["content_rating"] = "na"
    data["user_rating"] = "0"
    data["director"] = "na"
    data["writer"] = "na"
    data["primary_cast"] = "na"
    data["secondary_cast"] ="na"
    data["other_cast"] = "na"
    data["metascore"] = "0"
    data["meta_scored"] = "na"
    data["user_reviews"] = "0"
    data["user_critic"] = "0"
    data["plot_keywords"] = "na"
    data["genres"] = "na"
    data["country"] = "na"
    data["language"] = "na"
    data["filming_locations"] = "na"
    data["budget"] = "0"
    data["worldwide_gross"] = "0"
    data["runtime"] = "0"
    data["sound_mix"] = "na"

    r = requests.get(url)
    #print(r.text)
    soup = BeautifulSoup(bs_preprocess(r.text), 'html.parser')
   
    title_bar_items = soup.find("div",attrs={"class":"titleBar"})
    movie_title = title_bar_items.find("h1",attrs={"class":""})    
    if (not movie_title == None):
        #clean-up [b] - replace invalid character
        data["movie_title"] = movie_title.contents[0].replace(u'\xa0', u'')
    else:
        movie_title = title_bar_items.find("h1",attrs={"class":"long"})
        if (not movie_title == None):    
            data["movie_title"] = movie_title.contents[0].replace(u'\xa0', u'')
    
    year = title_bar_items.find("a", href=re.compile("year"))
    if (not year == None):
        data["year"] = year.string.strip()

    summary_text_item = soup.find("div",attrs={"class":"summary_text"})
    if (not summary_text_item == None):
        data["plot_summary"] = summary_text_item.text 
        
    user_rating = soup.find("span", {"itemprop" : "ratingValue"})
    if (not user_rating == None):
        data["user_rating"] = user_rating.string.strip()

    plot_summary_items = soup.find("div",attrs={"class":"plot_summary"})
    h4_items = plot_summary_items.find_all("h4", attrs={"class":"inline"})
    for item in h4_items:
        if (item.string == "Director:"):
            if (not item.next_sibling == None):
                #clean-up [c] - trim the leading and trailing whitespace in the values
                data["director"] = item.next_sibling.string.strip()
        elif (item.string == "Directors:"):
            if (not item.next_sibling == None):
                data["director"] = item.next_sibling.string.strip()
        elif (item.string == "Creator:"):
            if (not item.next_sibling == None):
                data["director"] = item.next_sibling.string.strip()
        elif (item.string == "Creators:"):
            if (not item.next_sibling == None):
                data["director"] = item.next_sibling.string.strip()
        elif (item.string == "Writer:"):
            if (not item.next_sibling == None):
                data["writer"] = item.next_sibling.string.strip()
        elif (item.string == "Writers:"):
            if (not item.next_sibling == None):
                data["writer"] = item.next_sibling.string.strip()
        elif (item.string == "Star:"):
            if (not item.next_sibling == None):
                data["primary_cast"] = item.next_sibling.string.strip()
        elif (item.string == "Stars:"):
            if (not item.next_siblings == None):
                for nextSibling in item.next_siblings:
                    nextSibling_value = nextSibling.string.strip()
                    if (not nextSibling_value == "," ) and (not nextSibling_value == "|") and (not nextSibling_value == "See full cast & crew") and (not nextSibling_value == ""):  
                        if (data["primary_cast"] == "na"):
                            data["primary_cast"] = nextSibling_value
                        elif (data["secondary_cast"] == "na"):
                            data["secondary_cast"] = nextSibling_value
                        elif (data["other_cast"] == "na"):
                            data["other_cast"] = nextSibling_value
                           
    metascore = soup.find("div",attrs={"class":"metacriticScore"})
    if (not metascore == None):
        data["metascore"] = metascore.string.strip()
        data["meta_scored"] = metascore["class"][1]

    title_review = soup.find("div",attrs={"class":"titleReviewBarItem titleReviewbarItemBorder"})     
    if (not title_review == None):
        user_reviews = title_review.find("a", href=re.compile("reviews"))
        if (not user_reviews == None):
            #clean-up [d] - remove decoration wording
            data["user_reviews"] = user_reviews.string.strip().replace(",","").replace(" user","").replace(" critic","")
        user_critic = title_review.find("a", href=re.compile("externalreviews"))
        if (not user_critic == None):
            data["user_critic"] = user_critic.string.strip().replace(",","").replace(" critic","").replace(" user","")

    json_script = json.loads(soup.find('script', type='application/ld+json').text)
    if (not json_script == None):
        if ("contentRating" in json_script): 
            data["content_rating"] = json_script['contentRating']        
        
    title_details_items = soup.find("div" ,attrs={"class":"article","id":"titleStoryLine"})
   
    if (data["content_rating"] == "na"):
        h4_items = title_details_items.find_all("h4" ,attrs={"class":"inline"})
        for item in h4_items:
            if (item.string == "Certificate:" ):
                if (not item.next_sibling == None): 
                    data["content_rating"] = item.next_sibling.string
                    if (data["content_rating"] == None):
                        data["content_rating"] = "na"            

    
    genre_items = title_details_items.find_all("a", href=re.compile("genres"))
    genre_count = 0
    for item in genre_items:
        if (genre_count == 0) :
            genre_count = 1
            genre_value = item.string.strip()        
        else:
            #clean-up [e] - concatenate multiple values in a single string
            genre_value = genre_value + '|' + item.string.strip()
    if (genre_count == 1) :
        data["genres"] = genre_value
    
    keyword_items = title_details_items.find_all("a", href=re.compile("keywords=")) 
    keyword_count = 0
    for item in keyword_items:
        if (keyword_count == 0) :
            keyword_count = 1
            keyword_value = item.string.strip()        
        else:
            keyword_value = keyword_value + '|' + item.string.strip()       
    if (keyword_count == 1) :
        data["plot_keywords"] = keyword_value


    title_details_items = soup.find("div",attrs={"class":"article","id":"titleDetails"})
    div_items = title_details_items.find_all("div", attrs={"class":"txt-block"})
    for div_item in div_items:
        item = div_item.find("h4")
        if(not item == None):
            if (item.string == "Country:"):
                if (not item.next_sibling == None):
                    data["country"] = item.next_sibling.string.strip()      
            elif (item.string == "Language:"):
                if (not item.next_sibling == None):
                    data["language"] = item.next_sibling.string.strip()  
            elif (item.string == "Filming Locations:"):
                if (not item.next_sibling == None):
                    data["filming_locations"] = item.next_sibling.string.strip()  
            elif (item.string == "Budget:"):
                if (not item.next_sibling == None):                   
                    if ("$" in item.next_sibling.string):
                        #clean-up [f] - remove dollar sign / curreny codes and comma from the money value
                        data["budget"] = float(item.next_sibling.string.strip().replace("$","").replace(",",""))
                    else:
                        input_currency = item.next_sibling.string.strip()[0:3]
                        converted_currency = input_currency.replace("RUR","RUB")
                        try:
                            #clean-up [g] - convert foreign currency to USD
                            rate = c.get_rate(converted_currency, 'USD')
                        except:
                            print(input_currency + "not available")
                            rate = 1
                        data["budget"] = float(item.next_sibling.string.strip().replace(input_currency,"").replace(",",""))*rate
                        
            elif (item.string == "Cumulative Worldwide Gross:"):
                if (not item.next_sibling == None):
                    if ("$" in item.next_sibling.string):
                        data["worldwide_gross"] = float(item.next_sibling.string.strip().replace("$","").replace(",",""))
                    else:
                        input_currency = item.next_sibling.string.strip()[0:3]
                        converted_currency = input_currency.replace("RUR","RUB")
                        try:
                            rate = c.get_rate(converted_currency, 'USD')
                        except:
                            print(input_currency + " not available")
                            rate = 1
                        data["worldwide_gross"] = float(item.next_sibling.string.strip().replace(input_currency,"").replace(",",""))*rate                    

            elif (item.string == "Runtime:"):
                if (not item.next_sibling == None):  
                    #clean-up [d] - remove decoration wording
                    data["runtime"] = item.next_sibling.string.strip().replace(" min","") 
            elif (item.string == "Sound Mix:"):
                if (not item.next_sibling == None):
                    data["sound_mix"] = item.next_sibling.string.strip()                  

    return data

"""
This is main cell which performs
1. create a dataframe which will store the scraped data of each movie
2. request the html content of https://www.imdb.com/search/title/ with parameters
    a. title_type - what type of film/series. 
    b. year_start - begin date of movie release
    c. year_end - end date of movie release
    d. page_count - how many "pages" of records to be extracted. There are 50 titles per page.
3. extract all movies' URLs
4. call and pass in each movie's URL to main function getMovieDetails to scrape the data 
5. store the scraped data of each movie into dataframe

we make few assumptions in this script
1. we extract "feature film" types only defined by IMDB, which includes those foreign films shown on USA TV only.
2. IMDB default sorts the feature film search record based on film popularity 
    which indicates how much that titles page has been visited. We extract the records in this default order.
    However, we assume the popularity <> movie rating and world gross. 
    We also assume it helps to remove those "unknown"/"outlier" films which tend to hava no rating and a lot missing values 
3. we will retrieve the data from the year 2015-2019 and 1000 titles for each year. 
    We believe it pretty covers both good and bad films in recent years.
4. we exclude year 2000 which the film industries have been impacted greatly by covid19 pandemic. 
    We consider 2020 as outlier year. 
5. we convert the budget and gross values into USD based on current market rate and ignore the effect of inflation.

"""

title_type = "feature"
#year_start = "2018-01-01"
#year_end = "2018-12-31"
year_start = ["2019-01-01","2018-01-01","2017-01-01","2016-01-01","2015-01-01"]
year_end = ["2019-12-31","2018-12-31","2017-12-31","2016-12-31","2015-12-31"]
rating_min = 1.0
rating_max = 10.0
vote_count = 500
page_count = 20

df_moviedetails = pd.DataFrame(columns=["movie_title", "year", "movie_url", "plot_summary", "content_rating", "user_rating", "director", "writer", "primary_cast", "secondary_cast", "other_cast", "metascore", "meta_scored", "user_reviews", "user_critic", "plot_keywords", "genres", "country", "language", "filming_locations", "budget", "worldwide_gross", "runtime", "sound_mix"])

start_processing_time = datetime.now()
#print(start_processing_time)

for year_index in range(0,len(year_start)):
    print("processing year" + year_start[year_index][:4])
    for page_index in range(0, page_count):
        #html_url = 'https://www.imdb.com/search/title/?year=2019-01-01,2019-12-31&view=simple&start='+ str((page_index*50)+1) + '&ref_=adv_nxt'
        #html_url = 'https://www.imdb.com/search/title/?title_type=feature&year=2019-01-01,2019-12-31&view=simple&start='+ str((page_index*50)+1) + '&ref_=adv_nxt'
        html_url = 'https://www.imdb.com/search/title/?title_type=%s&year=%s,%s&user_rating=%s,%s&num_votes=%s,&view=simple&start=%s'%(title_type, year_start[year_index], year_end[year_index], rating_min, rating_max, vote_count, str((page_index*50)+1)) + '&ref_=adv_nxt'
    
        print('processing page -' + str(page_index+1))

        html_response = requests.get(html_url)
        html_soup = BeautifulSoup(html_response.text, 'lxml')
        movie_links = [a.attrs.get('href') for a in html_soup.select('span.lister-item-header a')]
    
        for index in range(0, len(movie_links)):
            start_time = time.time()
        
            try:
                df_moviedetails = df_moviedetails.append(getMovieDetails('https://www.imdb.com'+movie_links[index]), ignore_index=True)
            except:
                print('Exception reported on ' + str(page_index+1) + '-' + str(index+1) + '-' + movie_links[index])
        
            print(str(index+1) + '-' + movie_links[index] + '--- %s seconds ---' % (time.time() - start_time))

end_processing_time = datetime.now()
time_delta = end_processing_time - start_processing_time
total_seconds = time_delta.total_seconds()
print(end_processing_time)
print('processing completed in ' + '--- %s minutes ---' %(total_seconds/60))        

"""
export dataframe into csv file
"""
df_moviedetails.to_csv (r'export_moviedetails_good.csv', encoding='utf-8-sig', index = False, header=True)
print(df_moviedetails.shape)
print(datetime.now())
print('csv exported!')

#We generate the word cloud from the successful movies' movie genres and plot keywords

comment_words = ""

for index, row in df_goodmovies.iterrows():
    
    separate = row['genres'].split("|") 
    for j in range(len(separate)): 
        separate[j] = separate[j].strip().lower() 
        
    comment_words += " ".join(separate)+" "
    
print(comment_words)

In [44]:
# Importing the Libraries
from wordcloud import WordCloud, STOPWORDS
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

stop_words = set(STOPWORDS)
# Creating the Word Cloud
final_wordcloud = WordCloud(width = 800, height = 800, 
                background_color ='black', 
                stopwords = stop_words, 
                min_font_size = 10).generate(comment_words)

# Displaying the WordCloud                    
plt.figure(figsize = (10, 10), facecolor = None) 
plt.imshow(final_wordcloud) 
plt.axis("off") 
plt.tight_layout(pad = 0) 
  
plt.show()
In [45]:
plotkeywords_list = ""

for index, row in df_goodmovies.iterrows():
    if (len(row['plot_keywords']) > 2):
        separate = row['plot_keywords'].replace("title"," ").split("|") 
        for j in range(len(separate)): 
            separate[j] = separate[j].strip().lower() 

        plotkeywords_list += " ".join(separate)+" "
    
print(plotkeywords_list)

In [47]:
"""
Using gensim's LdaModel, we build topic modeling based on LDA algorithm to discover the hidden commom story elements from the
successful movies' unstructured story plot summaries. 
Gensim is an open source open-source library for unsupervised topic modeling and natural language processing.

Before implementing a topic model, we use python's nltk (natural language toolkit) to preprocess the text, including tokenization, 
stop words and punctuation removal, lemmatization, stemming.

"""
import nltk
nltk.download('stopwords')
nltk.download('wordnet')
from nltk.corpus import stopwords
from nltk.stem.wordnet import WordNetLemmatizer
from nltk.stem.porter import PorterStemmer

import gensim
from gensim import corpora
import string
from pathlib import Path
from pprint import pprint


stop = set(stopwords.words('english'))

#addon to stop words
domain_stop = []
stop.update(domain_stop)

exclude = set(string.punctuation)
lemma = WordNetLemmatizer()
stemmer = PorterStemmer()

def clean(doc):
    punc_free = ''.join([ch for ch in doc.lower() if ch not in exclude])
    stop_free = ' '.join([i for i in punc_free.split() if i not in stop])
    normalized = ' '.join(lemma.lemmatize(word) for word in stop_free.split())
    stemmed = ' '.join(stemmer.stem(word) for word in normalized.split())
    stemmed_filter = ' '.join(word for word in stemmed.split() if len(word) > 2)
    return stemmed_filter

# loop thru each movie's plot summary like a document and call function clean(doc) to preprocess the text
doc_clean = [clean(doc).split() for doc in df_goodmovies["plot_summary"] ]

#This module implements the concept of a Dictionary  a mapping between words and their integer ids.
#Convert document (a list of words) into the bag-of-words format = list of (token_id, token_count) 2-tuples.
dictionary = corpora.Dictionary(doc_clean)
doc_term_matrix = [dictionary.doc2bow(doc) for doc in doc_clean]

# Compute Perplexity

"""
The code below will provide a matrix representing plot_summary text. 
It will be a sparse matrix with a large number of elements in a compressed sparse row format.
"""
from sklearn import preprocessing
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, confusion_matrix, f1_score
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier

from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfTransformer
from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import CountVectorizer
from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer

"""
6 lines of code below provide with a matrix representing the text. 
with Tfidftransformer computing word counts using CountVectorizer 
and then computing the IDF values and after that the Tf-IDF scores.

#count_vectorizer = CountVectorizer()
#count_vectorizer.fit_transform(x_df)
#freq_term_matrix = count_vectorizer.transform(x_df)

#tfidf = TfidfTransformer(norm = "l2")
#tfidf.fit(freq_term_matrix)
#tf_idf_matrix = tfidf.fit_transform(freq_term_matrix)
"""

# With Tfidfvectorizer can do all the three steps above at once.
tfidf_vectorizer=TfidfVectorizer(use_idf=True)
tf_idf_matrix=tfidf_vectorizer.fit_transform(x_df)

print(tf_idf_matrix)
